# A-Wiki — Cline Rules

> **FIRST: Read `AGENTS.md`** in the repo root — complete A-Wiki brain specification
> (Iron Laws, Cost Pyramid, Swarm Intelligence, Directory Structure, Scripts Index)
> Start-of-session safety check: run `python scripts/agent-preflight.py`.

---

## First 3 Commands

```bash
git pull --ff-only origin main
python3 scripts/agent-preflight.py
python3 scripts/verify-awiki-ready.py --skip-evals
```

## External Data Layer

- Heavy/raw/private files live outside git in Google Drive `A-Wiki-Data`.
- `drive/` and `raw/` are machine-local links created by `bash scripts/setup-local.sh`.
- Verify OS-specific setup with `python3 scripts/verify-cross-platform.py --build-vec`.
- Never edit or commit `raw/`, `drive/`, `.tmp/`, `.mcp.json`, `.codex/`, or `.claude/`.

---

## Brain Improvement Gate

Before changing A-Wiki brain capabilities, agent rules, skills, hooks, plugins, scripts, sync, or public-safe data policy, follow `docs/protocols/brain-improvement-gate.md`.

- Clear gain for A-Wiki as a second brain
- Lightweight reusable shape first: hook, skill, plugin, GitHub Action, symlink, script, protocol, local index, or multi-model parallel workflow
- Cost-first, cross-platform, cross-device
- Private/raw/secrets stay in gitignored `drive/`/`raw/`

---

## Cross-Agent Plan Handoff

- Before multi-step work or Plan Mode output, follow `docs/protocols/cross-agent-plan-handoff.md`
- Split work into resumable chunks with ID/status/files/verify/handoff note
- Read/update local `handoff.md` before pause, limit, or Agent/IDE switch

---

## About This Project

**A-Wiki** = Hybrid swarm intelligence + knowledge wiki brain.

- `wiki/` — core knowledge base, managed entirely by AI agents
- `raw/` — immutable source documents (Google Drive link), never edit
- `agent-skills/` — swarm protocol, Iron Laws, debug-mantra, git-safety
- `skills/` — Claude Code skills, Thai language skills, ECC ecosystem skills
- `scripts/wiki/` — wiki management (search, gen-index, query-graph)
- `scripts/swarm/` — swarm ops (delegate, agent-switch, update-model-roster)

---

## Iron Laws (UNBREACHABLE — ALL platforms)

1. **NO production code without a failing test first**
2. **NO bug fixing without root cause investigation first** (debug-mantra 4-step)
3. **If a parallel model violates #1 or #2 → DISCARD and REWRITE**
4. **`raw/` is immutable** — never edit or delete any file inside `raw/`
5. **Config files must not be edited without explicit permission** (AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md)

---

## Wiki Editing Rules

- Filenames: **kebab-case English only** (e.g. `mqtt-broker.md`, `gemini-flash.md`)
- Every factual claim needs a confidence marker:
  - `[training]` — from AI training data, unverified
  - `[verified YYYY-MM-DD]` — personally verified on that date
  - `[wiki]` — from another wiki page
  - `[notebooklm YYYY-MM-DD]` — verified via NotebookLM on that date
- Always update `log.md` after significant edits
- Always update `wiki/context/wiki-overview.md` after adding new pages
- Plan before implementing: if change affects >3 files, list them first
- For Plan Mode or multi-step work, chunk the plan and checkpoint local `handoff.md`

---

## Cost Pyramid (start at lowest level — move up only when needed)

| Level | Method | Command |
|-------|--------|---------|
| **-1** | Local FTS5 search (free, offline) | `python scripts/wiki/search-wiki.py "query"` |
| **0** | Hooks + context compaction | auto-runs on session start |
| **1** | Free API via dynamic roster | `bash scripts/swarm/delegate.sh "query"` |
| **2** | Cheap paid models | via delegate.sh with --tier 2 |
| **3** | Subagent (Haiku-class) | via Agent tool |
| **4** | Current AI (this session) | complex reasoning only |

**Model selection is always dynamic — never hard-code model names.**

```bash
cat wiki/context/model-roster.conf          # see current free models
bash scripts/update-model-roster.sh         # refresh from OpenRouter API
```

---

## Swarm Intelligence

Three roles — always use the cheapest adequate role:

- **Architect** (free reasoning model from roster) — planning, root cause, design
- **Executioner** (free fast model from roster) — code writing, tests, refactoring
- **Senior Critic** (YOU — primary agent) — validate ALL outputs, NOT delegatable

```bash
bash scripts/swarm/delegate.sh architect "design question"
bash scripts/swarm/delegate.sh executioner "implement X"
```

---

## Commit / Branch Rules

- **Commit directly to `main`** — NO branch, NO PR, NO worktree
- Commit format: `type(scope): description`
- Types: `feat` · `fix` · `docs` · `wiki` · `refactor` · `test` · `chore`
- Example: `wiki(iot): add MQTT broker entity page`

---

## Scripts Quick Reference

| Script | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `python scripts/wiki/search-wiki.py "q"` | FTS5 wiki search (Level -1) |
| `bash scripts/swarm/delegate.sh "q"` | Delegate to free model |
| `bash scripts/update-model-roster.sh` | Refresh free model list |
| `python scripts/gen-index.py` | Rebuild wiki index + FTS5 |
| `python scripts/wiki/query-graph.py --hubs` | Knowledge graph hubs |
| `bash scripts/setup-local.sh` | Full machine setup (run once) |

---

## Do NOT Delegate (Primary Agent ONLY)

- Deep reasoning / decision making
- Writing new wiki entity/concept pages
- Editing AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, or .clinerules
- Security review, schema edits
- Senior Critic validation (Iron Law #3)

---

